The paper deals with caching and multicasting in a network, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed scheme is decentralized, which falls under distributed computing (cs.DC) and self-organizing systems (cs.SI). The paper also involves content placement and overlap, which relates to data structures (cs.DS).
